HEADWORD: Flexor
<hw>Flex"or</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL.]</ety>
<fld>(Anat.)</fld> <def>A muscle which bends or flexes any part; <as>as,
the <ex>flexors</ex> of the arm or the hand</as>; -- opposed to
<contr>extensor</contr>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

